[2026-04-01] ZXL Compression Project — Day 1
============================================================

## Session Summary

### Project Goal
Design and implement a novel binary data compression algorithm called ZXL.

### Key Design Decisions
- Target: binary data (executables, structured binary, general binary)
- Language: C with SIMD intrinsics (x86-64 AVX2/SSE2)
- Core innovations agreed upon:
  1. Delta-aware LZ matching — exact match | XOR-delta match | additive-delta match
     (catches relocated addresses, incrementing counters, bit-shifted patterns)
  2. Entropy-weighted optimal parsing — pick match minimizing output bits, not just longest
  3. rANS entropy coding with context model
  4. SIMD-first data structure design (AVX2 256-bit lanes from ground up)

### Why Novel
- No mainstream compressor integrates XOR/additive delta matching inside the LZ engine
- Entropy-weighted parsing studied academically but not in a fast production compressor
- SIMD retrofitted in existing tools; ZXL designs around it from day 1

